Assignment 1: Lorenz Attractor
Name: Krishna Chaitanya Sripada

Key bindings:

q: Rotate X axis +
a: Rotate X axis -
w: Rotate Y axis +
s: Rotate Y axis -
e: Rotate Z axis +
d: Rotate Z axis -
r: Restart animation
f: Finish animation
t: Animation speed +
g: Animation speed -
UP: Rotate X axis +
DOWN: Rotate X axis -
LEFT: Rotate Y axis +
RIGHT: Rotate Y axis -
p: Lorenz Parameter b +
l: Lorenz Parameter b -
o: Lorenz Parameter s +
k: Lorenz Parameter s -
i: Lorenz Parameter r +
j: Lorenz Parameter r -

Optional: We found that for small values of r, the system is stable and evolves to one of two fixed point attractors. When r is larger than 24.74, the fixed points become repulsers and the trajectory is repelled by them in a very complex way.

To test this, reduce the value of parameter ‘r’ and then press the key ‘r’ to test the scenario mentioned above.

Time taken to complete the assignment: 8 hours
